Vice President Mike Pence spoke at the Latshaw Drilling Rig 45 in Midland, Texas, praising the American energy industry and the Permian Basin. He highlighted the Trump administration's support for American energy production and the rollback of regulations that hindered the industry. Pence also emphasized the importance of the United States-Mexico-Canada Agreement (USMCA) in promoting American energy and called on Congress to ratify the agreement. He commended the hard work and innovation of those in the energy sector and expressed confidence in the continued success of the Permian Basin. Pence concluded by affirming the administration's commitment to American greatness through faith, freedom, and natural resources.